@startuml 13-read-write-split
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 12

title Read-Write Splitting - The Stale Read Problem

actor "User" as user
participant "Proxy\n(ProxySQL)" as proxy
database "Master" as master
database "Slave" as slave

== Write Operation ==

user -> proxy : UPDATE profile SET name='Bob'
proxy -> master : Write
master --> proxy : OK
proxy --> user : Success!

== Read Operation (Stale Read) ==

user -> proxy : SELECT * FROM profile
proxy -> slave : Read (routed to slave)

note over slave #Pink
  Replication Lag!
  Slave hasn't received
  the UPDATE yet
end note

slave --> proxy : name='Alice' (old data!)
proxy --> user : Shows old data

note over user #Orange
  "Where's my update?!"
end note

note bottom
  Solutions:
  1. Force Master read after write
  2. Track write timestamp, route smart
  3. Accept staleness for non-critical data
end note

@enduml
